<br>
I always find it a little presumptous how people try to estimate the cost of anti-matter production when we haven't even dedicated any significant funding into researching manufacturing methods.  I'm a little reminded of how expensive processing aluminum used to be in the first half of the 19th Century (around $600 a pound) and now it's used to wrap sandwiches with.  I imagine anti-matter could take a similiar path.  Of course it'll still take a lot of energy to produce anti-matter but that's balanced out by the fact that you don't need a whole lot of it to zoom around the solar system with.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=197.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=197.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=197.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=197.topic&index=25><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=197.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.threadControl?topicID=197.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=197.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub97.ezbo